<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-21T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/284: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-21T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            21, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 21, 4 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your January 16, 7 p.m. Have spoken to His Excellency, Hsiung, and he
                                has authorized Chinese Minister by cable.</p>
                            <pb facs="0718" n="616" xml:id="pg_616"/>
                            <p>As the advance is provided for in the main contract,<note n="43" xml:id="d594fn43"><ref target="frus1917#pg_225"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p.
                                    225</ref>.</note> it is not clear what further negotiations
                                necessary except arranging details of the advance.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>